oad PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_6402049\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_6402049\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">März 21, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104xrv1710925958229.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xrv1710925958229.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xrv1710925958229.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xrv1710925958229\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The ProcScript code formatting feature allows you to correct or improve the code\n\t\tindentation and increase the code readability and understanding. As different organizations\n\t\tmay use different coding conventions, the following article explains how you can enforce the\n\t\tusage of the same rules across your organization.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xrv1710925958229__section_tsv_vzq_51c\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1163908e49\">Defining rules from a centralized location</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">To set custom formatting rules, you have to define a new subsection in the ASN file\n\t\t\t\tnamed <code class=\"ph codeph\">[FORMATTING]</code>. For more details, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kdp1710932019987.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kdp1710932019987.html\" title=\"The [FORMATTING] section of the assignment file allows you to assign rules and customize the code formatting tool in the Source Editor.\">[FORMATTING]</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">Under <code class=\"ph codeph\">[FORMATTING]</code>, you can add all rules. If a rule is not defined,\n\t\t\t\tthe default value is used. The <code class=\"ph codeph\">[FORMATTING]</code> rules are best placed\n\t\t\t\tin an ASN file that is used for your Project, that is, the default\n\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"ph filepath\">ide.asn</span> file, or your own ASN file. You can also use a\n\t\t\t\tseparate file that is included from your ASN file.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">For a separate file option, the file name and extension are not important. The file\n\t\t\t\tshould contain the <code class=\"ph codeph\">[FORMATTING]</code> header and the rules. The file can\n\t\t\t\tthen be included from any ASN file, using <code class=\"ph codeph\">#file</code>, for example -\n\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"ph filepath\">#file Z:\\rules\\rules.asn</span>, or <span class=\"ph filepath\">#file\n\t\t\t\t\tZ:\\.policy</span>. Ideally, the formatting rules should reside in a\n\t\t\t\tread-only location, so that you can enforce its usage across your organization.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"xrv1710925958229__note_emr_kvx_51c\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> We do not recommend including the  subsection in the environment of\n\t\t\t\tevery developer manually, as it can easily lead to errors and makes maintenance\n\t\t\t\tdifficult. A single ASN file in a network location is easier to maintain and share\n\t\t\t\tacross developers.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kdp1710932019987.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>[FORMATTING]</a><p>The [FORMATTING] section of the assignment file allows you to assign rules and customize the code formatting tool in the Source Editor.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_6402049\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_6402049\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Enforcing ProcScript Code Conventions Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated März 21, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 The ProcScript code formatting feature allows you to correct or improve the code indentation and increase the code readability and understanding. As different organizations may use different coding conventions, the following article explains how you can enforce the usage of the same rules across your organization. Defining rules from a centralized location To set custom formatting rules, you have to define a new subsection in the ASN file named [FORMATTING] . For more details, see [FORMATTING] . Under [FORMATTING] , you can add all rules. If a rule is not defined, the default value is used. The [FORMATTING] rules are best placed in an ASN file that is used for your Project, that is, the default ide.asn file, or your own ASN file. You can also use a separate file that is included from your ASN file. For a separate file option, the file name and extension are not important. The file should contain the [FORMATTING] header and the rules. The file can then be included from any ASN file, using #file , for example - #file Z:\\rules\\rules.asn , or #file Z:\\.policy . Ideally, the formatting rules should reside in a read-only location, so that you can enforce its usage across your organization. Note: We do not recommend including the subsection in the environment of every developer manually, as it can easily lead to errors and makes maintenance difficult. A single ASN file in a network location is easier to maintain and share across developers. Related Links [FORMATTING] The [FORMATTING] section of the assignment file allows you to assign rules and customize the code formatting tool in the Source Editor. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}